properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 6 at 10:25AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Florida...

Choctawhatchee River near Caryville (US 90) affecting Holmes and
Washington Counties
Choctawhatchee River near Bruce (SR 20) affecting Walton and
Washington Counties

The Flood Warning continues for
the Choctawhatchee River near Caryville (US 90).
* From late Friday night, or until the warning is cancelled.
* At  9:00 AM Thursday the stage was 7.7 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Flood stage is 14.0 feet.
* Forecast: Rise above flood stage by Saturday morning and continue
to rise to near 14.2 feet by early Sunday morning.
* Impact: At 14.0 feet: In Holmes County, Boat Ramp Road south of
CR-179 will flood. Access to several of the fish camps off Boat
Ramp Road may become inaccessible above this level.
properties.instruction:
All persons with interest along the river should monitor the latest
forecasts, and be prepared to take necessary precautions to protect
life and property. Do not drive cars through flooded areas. If you
see flood waters: Turn around. Don't drown.

For graphical hydrologic information, please go to weather.gov and
click on your state. Select Rivers and Lakes AHPS under current
conditions and click on your river point.
